    "rotation": 90,
    "text": "South Street, north side, east from Broad Street to Coenties Siip, showing buildings that face the East River. The Broad Street Hospital is at the left at Broad Street and the Seaman's Church Institute at Coenties Slip. The triangular park at the latter point is Jeanette Park. This was named after Jeannette Bennett, sister of James Gordon Bennett Sr., editor of the New York Herald, who financed an expedition to the Artic in 1879 with Lieutenant Commander George W. DeLong in command of the\n425 ton vessel \"Jeannette.\"\nBeyond is the Brooklyn Bridge.\nView 1: November 1927\nGeorge H. Balgue\nView 2: August 18, 1935\nP. L. Sperr\n",
    "text_source": "site",
